    "name": "Grid Independence Study — Richardson Extrapolation",
    "description": "A formal grid independence study was performed using three systematically refined meshes (coarse: 2.1M cells, medium: 5.8M cells, fine: 14.3M cells) following ASME V&V 20 procedures. Richardson extrapolation was applied to shear stress and velocity magnitude at 12 monitor planes. The Grid Convergence Index (GCI) was computed for all five flow-speed operating points. Results demonstrated monotonic convergence with GCI values below 2.3% for all quantities of interest, confirming that the medium mesh (5.8M cells) is sufficient for production simulations.",
